{{Politics of Gibraltar}}
The '''law of [[Gibraltar]]''' is a combination of [[Common law#History|common law]] 
and [[statute]], and is based heavily upon [[English law]].

The ''English Law (Application) Act'' of 1962 stipulates that English common law will apply to Gibraltar unless overridden by Gibraltar law. However, as Gibraltar is a [[self-governance|self-governing]] [[British overseas territories|British overseas territory]], it maintains its own independent [[tax law|tax status]] and its [[Gibraltar Parliament|parliament]] can enact laws independently of the [[United Kingdom]].

