{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
A '''politiquera''' in the United States is an individual who is paid for by an [[election]] [[Political campaign|campaign]] to knock on doors to issue [[Flyer (pamphlet)|flier]]s and encourage people to get out and vote in favour of the candidate. Candidates who generally lack the grass root [[Volunteering|volunteer]]s who normally do this job, resort to politiqueras to achieve the goal. Use of politiqueras in southern regions of Texas during the [[democratic primary]] on March 4, 2008 by [[Hillary Clinton]] campaign is one such example.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2008/05/13/us/politics/13streetcash.html?_r=1&ref=politics&oref=slogin Politiqueras in Hillary Clinton campaign in texas]</ref>

